																		I am trying to NOT necro
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="3087025"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1494106378 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 May 2017 21:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2812938">
									

<p>I am attempting to add my point of view on this&#8230;rainbow dimension? that is what I'm calling now.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;But&nbsp;hey,&nbsp;that's&nbsp;just&nbsp;a&nbsp;theory...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;A&nbsp;SCP&nbsp;theory!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>So, it obviously had heavy influence from two main sources: Catholicism (I see it resembling that denomination more than Lutheran, Baptist, et cetera) and good ol' Lovecraft. That Catholicism comes in the form of the government, or the society in general. Mr. Lovecraft gets his part with the creatures and the other worldly being.<br />
Personally I like this SCP and related article because (to me) it takes Christianity, and looks at how people could use the truth (my opinion) and pick and choose what part to believe to create the&#8230;.what should I name 093's religion? The Zoar. It creates the Zoar, a religion based off of a thing from another world&#8230;or time!<br />
So, I am probably crossing a line you never knew existed. I have thought up many theories for the Halo series, specifically explaining the Forerunners and Precursors.<br />
How is that relevant? Glad you asked. I am transplanting my theory that the Forerunners are human time travelers, into the being from the other world (BFOW for short) being a time traveler as well. Think about it. The BFOW obviously has advanced technology: travel, communication, weapons, bio-weapons/augmentations (the Tears). The BFOW also acts like no god I know, it wants its &quot;subjects&quot; to fight, then decides who are the true worthy by who remains alive.</p>
<p>So, the final part of my theory is that the Lovecraftian monsters are resultant not from an over purification via the Tears, but a brainwashing and over powered augmentation. The tears make the subject follow orders and laws, but also causes them to receive great strength and power, like the SCP-500 (the red pill I think) upgraded by SCP-914 (the&#8230;upgrade machine?) in the way it strengthens people. When the people were exposed to the PUREST form, it resulted in an overpowering of how the body normally acts. Not just that, it also resulted in a continuous following of their orders from the war (when they were created), to find and destroy all who oppose the quasi-america place&#8230;what ever it was call? And so, they continue to seek and destroy any and all who could pose even the SLIGHTEST threat to the state.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I post this, not because I think people will come back and find it, but because I hope to provide my theory to people looking here for the first time and because I need to vent my theories from time to time. I hope this is not considered a necro.<br />
Good day.</p>

							</div>

								
					
