			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-919198">
									

<p>Hard to rate this page, because I think the first half is fantastic, as is most of 093. The last log, though, almost ruined the entire SCP for me. It's way too much exposition, and it's not really in character. How did this other Foundation researcher find out so much all these modern Foundation expeditions couldn't? Further, how is he so intimately knowledgeably principally about events 300 years in the past in a dead world? To me, it's a giant out of characterism that really needs to be changed. I love this SCP to death, and that last entry just leaves me feeling let-down at the end :/</p>

